editorialSummary.text: Casual counter-serve chain serving a variety of chicken wings & sides.

originalText.text: The food is really good and I appreciate the many options they have but they fall short in a few aspects. One, the place is understaffed and asking for anything takes 5 minutes. The bathroom requires an employee to unlock it, they don’t have plastic straws just gross paper ones, and the tables are usually sticky or dirty. The place just feels like its slowly decaying and they forgot to give to me a cup for my soda, when I told them this I had to wait five minutes because the only cashier was busy helping an Uber Eats driver find his order…

originalText.text: Customer service was very short and snappy. I waited 40 minutes for a chicken sandwhich which takes 7 minutes to cook before asking how much longer. I was told the ticket wasn’t sent back….. this was very upsetting as the lady at the counter was very short with me. The resultant is also a mess! Tables are sticky and dirty. Also when the worker found out my order hadn't even been started she said in a demanding tone “come” to me….. this is not at all how an employee should speak to a customer. My friends were all in shock at the way I was being spoke to. Completely unprofessional.

originalText.text: We walked in and it was full of people. We were able to order our food with no issue, however we had to wait 30 long minutes for our food when they said it would take 15 short minutes. The presentation is nothing short of horrendous. My food was alright but the scent from my friends food drastically distorted his opinion on his meal. He was unable to finish his chicken tenders and we left unsatisfied. Don’t know how they get so many customers. Poor Baruch students eating such bad food.

originalText.text: The worst location I ever been to. The sprite tasted like seltzer water, the food lacked seasoning, tasted like fried chicken, fries tasted like grease. I needed salt so bad. I got different flavors and they tasted the same. I ordered the food to be done by 120. I came and the food was sitting for a least an hour. The fries were ice cold. The worst experience at wingstop. I feel like I was robbed for 18 dollars. I work in the area and if I had time I would’ve brought my food back. Where’s the manager. Trash trash trash.

originalText.text: ordered at 5pm with ETA of 30 minutes. started calling them and the deliveryman once it was 30 min late at 6pm. Kept calling them and they promised us that the food is coming out/is being delivered. It’s currently 9:25pm and they just cancelled on us without any notice. We ordered a significant amount of food and it doesn’t feel great to be lied to and scammed. Do not order from here if you want any kind of food. So disappointed.
